snippet: Hackers downloaded malicious software onto a test server, but did not steal any personal information on consumers, Obama administration officials said.

byline.original: By ROBERT PEAR and NICOLE PERLROTH
byline.contributor: Robert Pear reported from Washington, and Nicole Perlroth from San Francisco.

lead_paragraph: Hackers downloaded malicious software onto a test server, but did not steal any personal information on consumers, Obama administration officials said.

headline.print_headline: Hackers Breach Security of a Health Exchange Server
